Refs #15873 

Have the following snippet. Insert your snippet in a text, notice how the postCode is not being treated as a variable. It is being nicely treated as a variable if no default value is specified.

```js
provideCompletionItems(document, position, token) {
            
	    const mySnippet = new vscode.SnippetString();
            mySnippet.appendText('zurich ');
            mySnippet.appendVariable('postCode', '8008');
            
            const item = new vscode.CompletionItem('ZURICH', vscode.CompletionItemKind.Class);
            item.insertText = mySnippet;

            return [item];
        }
```

* enable `editor.formatOnSave`
* enable `files.autoSave: onFocusChange`
* have the launch.json below
* press add config button
* select nodejs launch
* 🐛 nothing happens


![dec-06-2016 15-05-50](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1794099/20928325/a6582234-bbc5-11e6-80b0-6aeeb1e6f1d6.gif)


